==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-chump.ogg|Audio (US)}}

=== Noun ===
'''chump''' (''plural'' '''chumps''')
# {{cattag|US|slang}} the opposite of a [[champ]]
#:''Buck up, man. Don't be such a '''chump'''.''
# the smaller of two [[bully|bullies]]
#: ''I'll take on that '''chump''', and you fight the other one.''
# an unintelligent person
#:''Don't ask him, he's just a '''chump'''.''
# a gullible person; someone easily taken advantage of, especially in the opinion of selfish or unscrupulous people
#:''It shouldn't be hard to put one over on ''that'' '''chump'''.''
#:''What a '''chump'''!  He could have kept that money!  Who would have known?''

====Synonyms====
